Nigerian musician, Joshua Olonitola, A.K.A Slim Joe, died on Sunday after complications with a kidney-related ailment, at age 30. The ‘O ti Yan Yan’ crooner was reported to have been seeking N15million for urgent medical intervention before he passed on. In an interview with The PUNCH on November 2021, the singer had said he had been diagnosed with end-stage kidney disease since November 24, 2020, and had been advised to go for a kidney transplant. In a sad turn of events, the singer has been reported dead on Sunday. One Kayode Jegede who claimed to be the cousin of the deceased confirmed his passing on Facebook. Jegede wrote, “I lost a cousin, Joshua Olonitola aka, Slim Joe of Oti yanyan fame. “Aburo, it is painful to lose a good brother like you to death at your prime of fame and age. “You made an impact in the world with the very short time you lived, you were such a brilliant boy growing up then. We shall all miss you.” Slim Joe dropped hit songs in the year 2018 which include “Jekajolepo” and “Packaging”.  He later featured Don Jazzy in “Jekajolepo” remix. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com